race.comment: ALLY (8) came with a huge finish to score first-up at Murwillumbah then was a bit flat last start at Doomben over today's trip. Very fit now after two runs back and the engagement of Angela Jones is a tick. In the right race to return to winning ways. Honest mare JOY A PLENTY (10) returned from a short spell with a close second over 1100m at Ipswich last time out. Surprisingly has a mediocre record here on her home track which is a concern, but from gate one she gets a cosy run and should be there at the business end. Track and trip specialist BOLD JULIUS (2) is in the mix despite his big weight, along with NEW HAMPSHIRE (7) who should be right at his peak third up.
